00459             break;
00460     }

01504             break;

01507     return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x000107000000C200ull);

01524 #if CVMX_ENABLE_CSR_ADDRESS_CHECKING
01525 static inline uint64_t CVMX_CIU_WDOGX(unsigned long offset)
01526 {
01527     switch(cvmx_get_octeon_family()) {
01528         case OCTEON_CN56XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01529             if ((offset <= 11))
01530                 return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001070000000500ull) + ((offset) & 15) * 8;
01531             break;
01532         case OCTEON_CN70XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01533         case OCTEON_CN52XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01534         case OCTEON_CNF71XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01535         case OCTEON_CN61XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01536             if ((offset <= 3))
01537                 return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001070000000500ull) + ((offset) & 3) * 8;
01538             break;
01539         case OCTEON_CN31XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01540         case OCTEON_CN50XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01541             if ((offset <= 1))
01542                 return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001070000000500ull) + ((offset) & 1) * 8;
01543             break;
01544         case OCTEON_CN38XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01545         case OCTEON_CN58XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01546             if ((offset <= 15))
01547                 return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001070000000500ull) + ((offset) & 15) * 8;
01548             break;
01549         case OCTEON_CN66XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01550             if ((offset <= 9))
01551                 return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001070000000500ull) + ((offset) & 15) * 8;
01552             break;
01553         case OCTEON_CN63XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01554             if ((offset <= 5))
01555                 return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001070000000500ull) + ((offset) & 7) * 8;
01556             break;
01557         case OCTEON_CN30XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01558             if ((offset == 0))
01559                 return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001070000000500ull) + ((offset) & 0) * 8;
01560             break;
01561         case OCTEON_CN78XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01562             if (OCTEON_IS_MODEL(OCTEON_CN78XX))
01563                 if ((offset <= 47))
01564                     return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001010000020000ull) + ((offset) & 63) * 8;
01565             if (OCTEON_IS_MODEL(OCTEON_CN78XX_PASS1_X))
01566                 if ((offset <= 47))
01567                     return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001010000020000ull) + ((offset) & 63) * 8;
01568 
01569             break;
01570         case OCTEON_CNF75XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01571         case OCTEON_CN73XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01572             if ((offset <= 15))
01573                 return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001010000020000ull) + ((offset) & 15) * 8;
01574             break;
01575         case OCTEON_CN68XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01576             if ((offset <= 31))
01577                 return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001070100100000ull) + ((offset) & 31) * 8;
01578             break;
01579     }
01580     cvmx_warn("CVMX_CIU_WDOGX (offset = %lu) not supported on this chip\n", offset);
01581     return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001010000020000ull) + ((offset) & 15) * 8;
01582 }
01583 #else
01584 static inline uint64_t CVMX_CIU_WDOGX(unsigned long offset)
01585 {
01586     switch(cvmx_get_octeon_family()) {
01587         case OCTEON_CN56XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01588             return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001070000000500ull) + (offset) * 8;
01589         case OCTEON_CN70XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01590         case OCTEON_CN52XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01591         case OCTEON_CNF71XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01592         case OCTEON_CN61XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01593             return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001070000000500ull) + (offset) * 8;
01594         case OCTEON_CN31XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01595         case OCTEON_CN50XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01596             return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001070000000500ull) + (offset) * 8;
01597         case OCTEON_CN38XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01598         case OCTEON_CN58XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01599             return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001070000000500ull) + (offset) * 8;
01600         case OCTEON_CN66XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01601             return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001070000000500ull) + (offset) * 8;
01602         case OCTEON_CN63XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01603             return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001070000000500ull) + (offset) * 8;
01604         case OCTEON_CN30XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01605             return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001070000000500ull) + (offset) * 8;
01606         case OCTEON_CN78XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01607             if (OCTEON_IS_MODEL(OCTEON_CN78XX))
01608                 return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001010000020000ull) + (offset) * 8;
01609             if (OCTEON_IS_MODEL(OCTEON_CN78XX_PASS1_X))
01610                 return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001010000020000ull) + (offset) * 8;
01611 
01612         case OCTEON_CNF75XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01613         case OCTEON_CN73XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01614             return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001010000020000ull) + (offset) * 8;
01615         case OCTEON_CN68XX & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK:
01616             return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001070100100000ull) + (offset) * 8;
01617     }
01618     return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001010000020000ull) + (offset) * 8;
01619 }
01620 #endif

05399 
05400 /**
05401  * cvmx_ciu_int#_en1
05402  *
05403  * Enables for CIU_SUM1_PPX_IPx  or CIU_SUM1_IOX_INT
05404  * CIU_INT0_EN1:  PP0/IP2
05405  * CIU_INT1_EN1:  PP0/IP3
05406  * CIU_INT2_EN1:  PP1/IP2
05407  * CIU_INT3_EN1:  PP1/IP3
05408  * CIU_INT4_EN1:  PP2/IP2
05409  * CIU_INT5_EN1:  PP2/IP3
05410  * CIU_INT6_EN1:  PP3/IP2
05411  * CIU_INT7_EN1:  PP3/IP3
05412  * - .....
05413  * (hole)
05414  * CIU_INT32_EN1: IO0 (PEM0)
05415  * CIU_INT33_EN1: IO1 (Reserved for o70)
05416  *
05417  * PPx/IP2 will be raised when...
05418  *
05419  * n = x*2
05420  * PPx/IP2 = |([CIU_SUM2_PPx_IP2,CIU_SUM1_PPx_IP2, CIU_INTn_SUM0] &
05421  * [CIU_EN2_PPx_IP2,CIU_INTn_EN1, CIU_INTn_EN0])
05422  *
05423  * PPx/IP3 will be raised when...
05424  *
05425  * n = x*2 + 1
05426  * PPx/IP3 =  |([CIU_SUM2_PPx_IP3,CIU_SUM1_PPx_IP3, CIU_INTn_SUM0] &
05427  * [CIU_EN2_PPx_IP3,CIU_INTn_EN1, CIU_INTn_EN0])
05428  *
05429  * PPx/IP4 will be raised when...
05430  * PPx/IP4 = |([CIU_SUM1_PPx_IP4, CIU_INTx_SUM4] & [CIU_INTx_EN4_1, CIU_INTx_EN4_0])
05431  *
05432  * PCI/INT will be raised when...
05433  *
05434  * PCI/INT0 (PEM0)
05435  * PCI/INT0 = |([CIU_SUM2_IO0_INT,CIU_SUM1_IO0_INT, CIU_INT32_SUM0] &
05436  * [CIU_EN2_IO0_INT,CIU_INT32_EN1, CIU_INT32_EN0])
05437  *
05438  * PCI/INT1 is reserved for o70.
05439  * PCI/INT1 = |([CIU_SUM2_IO1_INT,CIU_SUM1_IO1_INT, CIU_INT33_SUM0] &
05440  * [CIU_EN2_IO1_INT,CIU_INT33_EN1, CIU_INT33_EN0])
05441  */

05443     uint64_t u64;

09773 /**
09774  * cvmx_ciu_int#_sum0
09775  *
09776  * The remaining IP4 summary bits will be CIU_INTX_SUM4.
09777  * CIU_INT0_SUM0:  PP0/IP2
09778  * CIU_INT1_SUM0:  PP0/IP3
09779  * CIU_INT2_SUM0:  PP1/IP2
09780  * CIU_INT3_SUM0:  PP1/IP3
09781  * CIU_INT4_SUM0:  PP2/IP2
09782  * CIU_INT5_SUM0:  PP2/IP3
09783  * CIU_INT6_SUM0:  PP3/IP2
09784  * CIU_INT7_SUM0:  PP3/IP3
09785  *  - .....
09786  * (hole)
09787  * CIU_INT32_SUM0: IO 0 (PEM0).
09788  * CIU_INT33_SUM0: IO 1 (Reserved in o70, in seperate address group)
09789  */
09790 union cvmx_ciu_intx_sum0 {
09791     uint64_t u64;
09792     struct cvmx_ciu_intx_sum0_s {

09808                                                          See UAHC0_EHCI_USBSTS UAHC0_OHCI0_HCINTERRUPTSTATUS */

09810                                                          When CIU_TIM_MULTI_CAST[EN] == 0, this interrupt is
09811                                                          common for all PP/IRQs, writing '1' to any PP/IRQ
09812                                                          will clear all TIMERx(x=0..9) interrupts.

09834                                                          and corresponding enable bit in CIU_INTx_EN is set
09835                                                          PPs use CIU_INTx_SUM0 where x=0-7

09838                                                          result and does not have a corresponding enable
09839                                                          bit, so does not directly contribute to

10972                                                          When CIU_TIM_MULTI_CAST[EN] == 0, this interrupt is

10974                                                          will clear all TIMERx(x=0..9) interrupts.
10975                                                          When CIU_TIM_MULTI_CAST[EN] == 1, TIMERx(x=0..9)

10978                                                          The combination of this field and the
10979                                                          CIU_SUM2_*[TIMER] field implement all 10 CIU_TIM*
10980                                                          interrupts. */
10981     uint64_t sum2                         : 1;  /**< SUM2&EN2 SUMMARY bit
10982                                                          This read-only bit reads as a one whenever any
10983                                                          CIU_SUM2_PPX_IPx (CIU_SUM2_IOX_INT)  bit is set
10984                                                          and corresponding enable bit in CIU_EN2_PPX_IPx
10985                                                          (CIU_EN2_IOX_INT) is set.
10986                                                          Note that WDOG_SUM only summarizes the SUM2/EN2
10987                                                          result and does not have a corresponding enable
10988                                                          bit, so does not directly contribute to
10989                                                          interrupts. */

10991                                                          Set any time PIP/IPD drops a packet */
10992     uint64_t gmx_drp                      : 2;  /**< GMX packet drop interrupt
10993                                                          Set any time corresponding GMX drops a packet */
10994     uint64_t trace                        : 1;  /**< Trace buffer interrupt
10995                                                          See TRA_INT_STATUS */
10996     uint64_t rml                          : 1;  /**< RML Interrupt
10997                                                          This bit is set when any bit is set in
10998                                                          CIU_BLOCK_INT. */
10999     uint64_t twsi                         : 1;  /**< TWSI Interrupt
11000                                                          See MIO_TWS0_INT */
11001     uint64_t wdog_sum                     : 1;  /**< SUM1&EN1 summary bit
11002                                                          This read-only bit reads as a one whenever any
11003                                                          CIU_SUM1_PPX_IPx (CIU_SUM1_IOX_INT)  bit is set
11004                                                          and corresponding enable bit in CIU_INTx_EN is set
11005                                                          PPs use CIU_INTx_SUM0 where x=0-19
11006                                                          PCIe uses the CIU_INTx_SUM0 where x=32-33.
11007                                                          Note that WDOG_SUM only summarizes the SUM1/EN1
11008                                                          result and does not have a corresponding enable
11009                                                          bit, so does not directly contribute to
11010                                                          interrupts. */
11011     uint64_t pci_msi                      : 4;  /**< PCIe MSI
11012                                                          See SLI_MSI_RCVn for bit <40+n> */
11013     uint64_t pci_int                      : 4;  /**< PCIe INTA/B/C/D
11014                                                          Refer to "Receiving Emulated INTA/INTB/
11015                                                          INTC/INTD" in the SLI chapter of the spec
11016                                                          PCI_INT<3> = INTD
11017                                                          PCI_INT<2> = INTC
11018                                                          PCI_INT<1> = INTB
11019                                                          PCI_INT<0> = INTA */

11021                                                          See MIO_UARTn_IIR[IID] for bit <34+n> */
11022     uint64_t mbox                         : 2;  /**< Two mailbox interrupts for entries 0-5
11023                                                          [33] is the or of <31:16>
11024                                                          [32] is the or of <15:0> */
11025     uint64_t gpio                         : 16; /**< 16 GPIO interrupts
11026                                                          When GPIO_MULTI_CAST[EN] == 1
11027                                                          Write 1 to clear either the per PP interrupt or
11028                                                          common GPIO interrupt for all PP/IOs,depending
11029                                                          on mode setting. This will apply to all 16 GPIOs.
11030                                                          See GPIO_MULTI_CAST for all details
11031                                                          When GPIO_MULTI_CAST[EN] == 0
11032                                                          Read Only, retain the same behavior as o63. */
11033     uint64_t workq                        : 16; /**< 16 work queue interrupts
11034                                                          See POW_WQ_INT[WQ_INT]
11035                                                           1 bit/group. A copy of the R/W1C bit in the POW. */
11036 #else

11046     uint64_t trace                        : 1;

11293                                                          CIU_SUM2_PPX_IPx (CIU_SUM2_IOX_INT)  bit is set
11294                                                          and corresponding enable bit in CIU_EN2_PPX_IPx
11295                                                          (CIU_EN2_IOX_INT) is set.
11296                                                          Note that WDOG_SUM only summarizes the SUM2/EN2
11297                                                          result and does not have a corresponding enable
11298                                                          bit, so does not directly contribute to
11299                                                          interrupts. */
11300     uint64_t ipd_drp                      : 1;  /**< IPD QOS packet drop interrupt
11301                                                          Set any time PIP/IPD drops a packet */
11302     uint64_t reserved_49_49               : 1;
11303     uint64_t gmx_drp                      : 1;  /**< GMX packet drop interrupt
11304                                                          Set any time corresponding GMX drops a packet */
11305     uint64_t trace                        : 1;  /**< Trace buffer interrupt
11306                                                          See TRA_INT_STATUS */
11307     uint64_t rml                          : 1;  /**< RML Interrupt
11308                                                          This bit is set when any bit is set in
11309                                                          CIU_BLOCK_INT. */
11310     uint64_t twsi                         : 1;  /**< TWSI Interrupt
11311                                                          See MIO_TWS0_INT */
11312     uint64_t wdog_sum                     : 1;  /**< SUM1&EN1 summary bit
11313                                                          This read-only bit reads as a one whenever any
11314                                                          CIU_SUM1_PPX_IPx (CIU_SUM1_IOX_INT)  bit is set
11315                                                          and corresponding enable bit in CIU_INTx_EN is set
11316                                                          PPs use CIU_INTx_SUM0 where x=0-19
11317                                                          PCIe uses the CIU_INTx_SUM0 where x=32-33.
11318                                                          Note that WDOG_SUM only summarizes the SUM1/EN1
11319                                                          result and does not have a corresponding enable
11320                                                          bit, so does not directly contribute to
11321                                                          interrupts. */
11322     uint64_t pci_msi                      : 4;  /**< PCIe MSI
11323                                                          See SLI_MSI_RCVn for bit <40+n> */
11324     uint64_t pci_int                      : 4;  /**< PCIe INTA/B/C/D
11325                                                          Refer to "Receiving Emulated INTA/INTB/
11326                                                          INTC/INTD" in the SLI chapter of the spec
11327                                                          PCI_INT<3> = INTD
11328                                                          PCI_INT<2> = INTC
11329                                                          PCI_INT<1> = INTB
11330                                                          PCI_INT<0> = INTA */
11331     uint64_t uart                         : 2;  /**< Two UART interrupts
11332                                                          See MIO_UARTn_IIR[IID] for bit <34+n> */
11333     uint64_t mbox                         : 2;  /**< Two mailbox interrupts for entries 0-5
11334                                                          [33] is the or of <31:16>
11335                                                          [32] is the or of <15:0> */
11336     uint64_t gpio                         : 16; /**< 16 GPIO interrupts
11337                                                          When GPIO_MULTI_CAST[EN] == 1
11338                                                          Write 1 to clear either the per PP interrupt or
11339                                                          common GPIO interrupt for all PP/IOs,depending
11340                                                          on mode setting. This will apply to all 16 GPIOs.
11341                                                          See GPIO_MULTI_CAST for all details
11342                                                          When GPIO_MULTI_CAST[EN] == 0
11343                                                          Read Only, retain the same behavior as o63. */
11344     uint64_t workq                        : 16; /**< 16 work queue interrupts
11345                                                          See POW_WQ_INT[WQ_INT]
11346                                                           1 bit/group. A copy of the R/W1C bit in the POW. */
11347 #else
11348     uint64_t workq                        : 16;
11349     uint64_t gpio                         : 16;
11350     uint64_t mbox                         : 2;
11351     uint64_t uart                         : 2;
11352     uint64_t pci_int                      : 4;
11353     uint64_t pci_msi                      : 4;
11354     uint64_t wdog_sum                     : 1;
11355     uint64_t twsi                         : 1;
11356     uint64_t rml                          : 1;
11357     uint64_t trace                        : 1;
11358     uint64_t gmx_drp                      : 1;
11359     uint64_t reserved_49_49               : 1;
11360     uint64_t ipd_drp                      : 1;
11361     uint64_t sum2                         : 1;
11362     uint64_t timer                        : 4;
11363     uint64_t usb                          : 1;
11364     uint64_t pcm                          : 1;
11365     uint64_t mpi                          : 1;
11366     uint64_t twsi2                        : 1;
11367     uint64_t powiq                        : 1;
11368     uint64_t ipdppthr                     : 1;

11371 #endif

11710     uint64_t gmx_drp                      : 2;  /**< GMX packet drop interrupt
11711                                                          Set any time corresponding GMX drops a packet */
11712     uint64_t reserved_47_46               : 2;
11713     uint64_t twsi                         : 1;  /**< TWSI Interrupt
11714                                                          See MIO_TWS0_INT */
11715     uint64_t wdog_sum                     : 1;  /**< SUM1&EN1 summary bit
11716                                                          This read-only bit reads as a one whenever any
11717                                                          CIU_SUM1_PPX_IPx bit is set and corresponding
11718                                                          enable bit in CIU_INTx_EN is set, where x
11719                                                          is the same as x in this CIU_INTx_SUM0.
11720                                                          PPs use CIU_INTx_SUM0 where x=0-7.
11721                                                          PCIe uses the CIU_INTx_SUM0 where x=32-33.
11722                                                          Note that WDOG_SUM only summarizes the SUM1/EN1
11723                                                          result and does not have a corresponding enable
11724                                                          bit, so does not directly contribute to
11725                                                          interrupts. */
11726     uint64_t pci_msi                      : 4;  /**< PCIe MSI
11727                                                          See SLI_MSI_RCVn for bit <40+n> */
11728     uint64_t pci_int                      : 4;  /**< PCIe INTA/B/C/D
11729                                                          Refer to "Receiving Emulated INTA/INTB/
11730                                                          INTC/INTD" in the SLI chapter of the spec
11731                                                          PCI_INT<3> = INTD
11732                                                          PCI_INT<2> = INTC
11733                                                          PCI_INT<1> = INTB
11734                                                          PCI_INT<0> = INTA */
11735     uint64_t uart                         : 2;  /**< Two UART interrupts
11736                                                          See MIO_UARTn_IIR[IID] for bit <34+n> */
11737     uint64_t mbox                         : 2;  /**< A read-only copy of CIU_PCI_INTA[INT] */
11738     uint64_t gpio                         : 16; /**< 16 GPIO interrupts
11739                                                          When GPIO_MULTI_CAST[EN] == 1
11740                                                          Write 1 to clear either the per PP or common GPIO
11741                                                          edge-triggered interrupts,depending on mode.
11742                                                          See GPIO_MULTI_CAST for all details.
11743                                                          When GPIO_MULTI_CAST[EN] == 0
11744                                                          Read Only, retain the same behavior as o63. */
11745     uint64_t workq                        : 16; /**< 16 work queue interrupts
11746                                                          See POW_WQ_INT[WQ_INT]
11747                                                          1 bit/group. A copy of the R/W1C bit in the POW. */
11748 #else
11749     uint64_t workq                        : 16;
11750     uint64_t gpio                         : 16;
11751     uint64_t mbox                         : 2;
11752     uint64_t uart                         : 2;
11753     uint64_t pci_int                      : 4;
11754     uint64_t pci_msi                      : 4;
11755     uint64_t wdog_sum                     : 1;
11756     uint64_t twsi                         : 1;
11757     uint64_t reserved_47_46               : 2;
11758     uint64_t gmx_drp                      : 2;
11759     uint64_t ipd_drp                      : 1;
11760     uint64_t sum2                         : 1;
11761     uint64_t timer                        : 4;
11762     uint64_t reserved_56_56               : 1;

11764     uint64_t mpi                          : 1;
11765     uint64_t twsi2                        : 1;

11769     uint64_t bootdma                      : 1;
11770 #endif
11771     } cn70xx;
11772     struct cvmx_ciu_int33_sum0_cn70xx     cn70xxp1;

13033  *
13034  * CIU_PP_POKE for CIU_WDOG
13035  *
13036  */
13037 union cvmx_ciu_pp_pokex {
13038     uint64_t u64;
13039     struct cvmx_ciu_pp_pokex_s {
13040 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
13041     uint64_t poke                         : 64; /**< Core poke. Writing any value to this register does the following:
13042                                                          * clears any pending interrupt generated by the associated watchdog.
13043                                                          * resets CIU_WDOG()[STATE] to 0x0.
13044                                                          * sets CIU_WDOG()[CNT] to ( CIU_WDOG()[LEN] << 8).
13045                                                          Reading this register returns the associated CIU_WDOG() register. */
13046 #else
13047     uint64_t poke                         : 64;
13048 #endif

13089 /**

13092  * This register contains the reset control for each core. A 1 holds a core in reset, 0 release
13093  * from reset. It resets to all ones when REMOTE_BOOT is enabled or all ones excluding bit 0 when
13094  * REMOTE_BOOT is disabled. Writes to this register should occur only if the CIU_PP_RST_PENDING
13095  * register is cleared.

13224 /**
13225  * cvmx_ciu_pp_rst_pending
13226  *
13227  * This register contains the reset status for each core.
13228  *
13229  */
13230 union cvmx_ciu_pp_rst_pending {
13231     uint64_t u64;
13232     struct cvmx_ciu_pp_rst_pending_s {
13233 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
13234     uint64_t reserved_48_63               : 16;
13235     uint64_t pend                         : 48; /**< Set if corresponding core is waiting to change its reset state. Normally a reset change
13236                                                          occurs immediately but if RST_PP_POWER[GATE] bit is set and the core is released from
13237                                                          reset a delay of 64K core clocks between each core reset will apply to satisfy power
13238                                                          management. */
13239 #else
13240     uint64_t pend                         : 48;
13241     uint64_t reserved_48_63               : 16;
13242 #endif
13243     } s;

13247 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
13248     uint64_t reserved_16_63               : 48;
13249     uint64_t pend                         : 16; /**< Set if corresponding core is waiting to change its reset state. Normally a reset change
13250                                                          occurs immediately but if RST_PP_POWER[GATE] bit is set and the core is released from
13251                                                          reset a delay of 64K core clocks between each core reset will apply to satisfy power
13252                                                          management.
13253                                                          The upper bits of this field remain accessible but will have no effect if the cores
13254                                                          are disabled. The number of bits cleared in CIU_FUSE[FUSE] indicate the number of cores. */

13258 #endif

16803 /**

16815     uint64_t en                           : 1;  /**< General Timer Interrupt Mutli-Cast mode:
16816                                                          - 0: Timer interrupt is common for all PP/IRQs.

16819                                                             to be done Individually based on per cnMIPS core.
16820                                                           Timer interrupts for IOs (X=32,33) will always use

16845     uint64_t dstop                        : 1;  /**< Debug-stop enable. */
16846     uint64_t cnt                          : 24; /**< Number of 1024-cycle intervals until next watchdog expiration. Cleared on write to
16847                                                          associated CIU_PP_POKE() register. */
16848     uint64_t len                          : 16; /**< Watchdog time-expiration length. The most-significant 16 bits of a 24-bit decrementer that
16849                                                          decrements every 1024 cycles. Must be set > 0. */
16850     uint64_t state                        : 2;  /**< Watchdog state. The number of watchdog time expirations since last core poke. Cleared on
16851                                                          write to associated CIU_PP_POKE() register. */
16852     uint64_t mode                         : 2;  /**< Watchdog mode:
16853                                                          0x0 = Off.
16854                                                          0x1 = Interrupt only.
16855                                                          0x2 = Interrupt + NMI.
16856                                                          0x3 = Interrupt + NMI + soft reset. */
16857 #else
16858     uint64_t mode                         : 2;
16859     uint64_t state                        : 2;
16860     uint64_t len                          : 16;
16861     uint64_t cnt                          : 24;
16862     uint64_t dstop                        : 1;
16863     uint64_t gstopen                      : 1;
16864     uint64_t reserved_46_63               : 18;
16865 #endif
16866     } s;
